"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is setting the major locator to MonthLocator and then immediately overriding it by setting the xticks to the unique dates in the dataframe. This will cause the dates to not be spaced out according to the MonthLocator. Instead, the xticks should be automatically generated by the MonthLocator.\",\n  \"patch\": \"19,20c19\\n< ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n< ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n---\\n> fig.autofmt_xdate(rotation=45)\\n\"\n}"